column1: #Text=# XTR: Rethinking the Role of Token Retrieval in Multi-Vector Retrieval
#Text=In this repository, we provide how you can run XTR (conteXtualized Token Retriever) for document retrieval.
#Text=Please refer to our NeurIPS 2023 paper ([Lee et al., 2023](https://arxiv.org/abs/2304.01982)) for technical details.
#Text=For instance, you can load XTR checkpoints as follows:
#Text=import tensorflow_text as text  # Registers the ops.
#Text=sample_texts = tf.constant(["dog", "Puppies are nice.", "I enjoy taking long walks along the beach with my dog."])
#Text=# This returns token-level representations from XTR.
#Text=See the licenses for the specific language governing
#Text=This is not an official Google product.
